Project: Restaurant Call Queue Management System (Exotel Trial Number Demo)
Overview

Build a production-quality restaurant call queue management platform for a Mandhi restaurant.

This system will use an Exotel Trial Voice Number for demonstration purposes.

The objective is to show how incoming customer calls are managed when only one employee is available to answer calls.

This is NOT an AI project.

Do NOT implement:

AI agents
Speech-to-text
Text-to-speech
LLM integrations
Order extraction
Chatbots

Focus entirely on telephony event handling, queue management, live monitoring, analytics, and call tracking.

Business Problem

The restaurant currently receives customer orders via phone calls.

"The system must support multiple employees. Incoming calls should be automatically assigned to the longest-idle AVAILABLE employee. If no employees are AVAILABLE, callers are placed into a FIFO queue. When an employee becomes AVAILABLE or completes a call, the oldest waiting caller should be assigned automatically."

When multiple customers call simultaneously:

One customer should be connected.
Additional customers should be placed in a queue.
Queue positions should be tracked.
Call history should be stored.
Management should have visibility into call activity.

The system must later support real Exotel production deployment using the restaurant's actual phone number.

For this demo, use only an Exotel Trial Voice Number.

